wiki.summary: "LLC" is a song by Nicki Minaj from her fourth studio album Queen . During the second episode of Queen Radio with Beats 1, Minaj revealed that "LLC" is one of her favorites from the album, and that Jay-Z inspired her to re-write the song after he stated she "went hard on the third verse" rather than commending the whole record, this inspired her to re-write it. Nicki plays up with her signature alter ego Roman Zolanski flow on this track, rapping about the standard she’s set for female rap and her accolades. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "LLC" is a song by Nicki Minaj from her fourth studio album Queen . During the second episode of Queen Radio with Beats 1, Minaj revealed that "LLC" is one of her favorites from the album, and that Jay-Z inspired her to re-write the song after he stated she "went hard on the third verse" rather than commending the whole record, this inspired her to re-write it. Nicki plays up with her signature alter ego Roman Zolanski flow on this track, rapping about the standard she’s set for female rap and her accolades. Referencing “Look What You Made Me Do” of Taylor Swift and other popular artists/singers like Britney Spears, Ariana Grande and Katy Perry. ”One of my favorites from the album just for skill, breath control, precision, and raising the bar. Jay heard the song and said, ‘You went hard on that 3rd verse.’ I’m such a perfectionist because he said third verse and not the song, I rewrote the whole thing. It’s important to me that the greats know time was spent making this album.” Read more on Last.fm.
